---

<section class="map-section" id="find-site" aria-labelledby="map-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 id="map-heading" class="display map-section__title">Where Gus was found</h2>
    <p class="map-section__text">
      Western South Dakota — private ranchland where Gary "Gus" Licking and Theropoda Expeditions documented a complex Late Cretaceous fossil bed.
    </p>
    <figure class="map-section__figure card">
      <img
        src="/images/Image%2013.jpeg"
        alt="Maps of the United States and South Dakota highlighting Harding County, the Gus discovery area in northwest South Dakota"
        class="map-section__img"
        loading="lazy"
        width="1672"
        height="941"
      />
      <figcaption>Harding County, South Dakota — Gus discovery area. General overview map, not an exact ranch parcel map.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .map-section {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .map-section__title {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .map-section__text {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    max-width: 42ch;
    color: var(--clay);
  }

  .map-section__figure {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .map-section__img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 1px);
  }

  .map-section__figure figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.65rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--clay);
  }
</style>
